h:493px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b706875ce4.PNG\" style=\"height:79px; width:476px\" /></p>\r\n',14,1,13158,34,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:21:34','2019','3','Nigerian tailor,Nigeria',NULL,'2019-03-27 13:46:17','2019-03-27 21:27:28',1,1,NULL),(166706,'Physically challenged persons stage massive protest inÂ Bayelsa State over non-Inclusion in civil service (Photos)','physically-challenged-persons-stage-massive-protest-in-bayelsa-state-over-non-inclusion-in-civil-service-photos','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Physically challenged persons stage massive protest inÂ Bayelsa State over non-Inclusion In civil service (Photos)\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b729336fac.JPG\" style=\"height:310px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>People&nbsp;living with disability in Bayelsa State, under the aegis of the Joint National Association of People Living with Disabilities have taken&nbsp;to the streets to press home their demand for inclusion in the recent employment of 1,000 graduates into the civil service. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>More than 200 physically challenged persons took part in the protest, which caused traffic gridlock in the Ovom axis of Yenagoa, the state capital, compelling motorists to take other routes.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b726360122.JPG\" style=\"height:331px; width:450px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The aggrieved persons, led by Comrade Eric Ikilowei, the group&#39;s state acting Chairman, blocked the entrance to the Government House, displaying placards with various inscriptions, and requested to speak with the Governor. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Addressing the press, Ikilowei stated: &quot;We are only demanding the employment of seven of our members who are graduates and this is not even up to the seven per cent or more that should have been our constitutional quota and right.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We have made our request known to the government on several fora, but they still keep blank ears to our plight. We have as much right as our counterparts, who are able indigenes. So, we should not be short-changed! We had embarked on several protests earlier to no avail.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b727a79b6c.JPG\" style=\"height:343px; width:450px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;We are giving the government a week&#39;s ultimatum to grant us employment or we shall come back by Monday for a bigger protest to shut down this government house and the whole state until our demands are granted.&quot; &nbsp;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>The protesters were addressed by some government officials, including the aide-de-camp to the governor, chief whip of BYHA, Hon. Tonye Emmanuel Isenah, the Commissioner for Empowerment and Social Welfare, Honourable Faith Opene, who assured the protesters that their requests for employment have already been looked into.</p>\r\n',12,1,521,4,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:26:47','2019','3','Bayelsa State,civil service ,massive protest,Physically challenged persons',NULL,'2019-03-27 13:55:34','2019-03-27 21:24:37',1,1,NULL),(166707,'Social media users drag a lecturer\'s assistant after he revealed why he refused to score a brilliant student an A','social-media-users-drag-a-lecturers-assistant-after-he-revealed-why-he-refused-to-score-a-brilliant-student-an-a','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b72896a3b5.PNG\" style=\"height:279px; width:503px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>A man has been slammed by social media users after he went on Facebook to boast about scoring a brilliant student 69 instead of the 70 marks he deserved.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mfoniso Isong wrote:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>&quot;Give am 70 na, a subtle, but still voice told me&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>It was my good side, but i just decided to ignore it</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Early last year, a lecturer friend asked me to help him mark some exam scripts</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I jumped in and did exactly what was on my mind</p>\r\n\r\n<p>So, there is this particular student that had 70, but I decided to give him 69</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I felt happy and fulfilled. I mean, me think that if i give this dude 70, he will go and testify in church about how he prayed fervently and all of that. He will go on and brag how brilliant he has always been</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See, I&#39;m not that wicked, I just like people sitting up</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b72896a3b5.PNG\" style=\"height:279px; width:503px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Social media users were outraged by his revelation and they called him out for it.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>See reactions&nbsp;below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b72ac38b87.PNG\" style=\"height:561px; width:493px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b72b64937a.PNG\" style=\"height:159px; width:476px\" /></p>\r\n',14,1,4834,20,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:30:40','2019','3','wicked,brilliant student ,Mfoniso Isong',NULL,'2019-03-27 13:56:46','2019-03-27 21:27:28',1,1,NULL),(166708,'Trump remains one of the best things that has ever happened to America and the world - FFK','trump-remains-one-of-the-best-things-that-has-ever-happened-to-america-and-the-world-ffk','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Despite the bad press that he is constantly subjected to, Trump remains one of the best things that has ever happened to America and the world - FFK\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b73e9665b5.JPG\" style=\"height:251px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As tweeted by former aviation minister, Femi Fani Kayode.</p>\r\n',12,1,2851,37,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:31:09','2019','3','ffk,trump,america,aviation minister,femi fani kayode',NULL,'2019-03-27 14:01:08','2019-03-27 21:27:02',1,1,NULL),(166709,'\'Thereâs a lot of money in Nollywood, houses, cars, and rolex back to back by many actors\' - Noble Igwe, fires shot on TwitterÂ ','theres-a-lot-of-money-in-nollywood-houses-cars-and-rolex-back-to-back-by-many-actors-noble-igwe-fires-shot-on-twitter','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\'Thereâs a lot of money in Nollywood, houses, cars, and rolex back to back by many actors\' - Noble Igwe, fires shot on Twitter\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b752cc1ffa.PNG\" style=\"border:0px solid black; height:399px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-top:0px; width:360px\" vspace=\"0\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Media personality, <strong>Noble Igwe</strong> dropped a subliminal tweet following the news of Nollywood actress, 19-year old <strong>Regina Daniels,&nbsp;</strong>who supposedly purchased two Mercedes Benz whips, &nbsp;a house for her mother and N3.3 million Rolex watch within space of one month.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The father of one wrote: &#39;There&rsquo;s a lot of money in Nollywood.Houses and cars back to back by manny actors.Cars, Rolex and shii. I&rsquo;m so happy for Nollywood.&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>#<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b754fc631b.PNG\" style=\"height:242px; width:579px\" /><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n',13,1,6168,35,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:32:59','2019','3','Regina Daniels,Noble Igwe,Nollywood, houses, cars, rolex',NULL,'2019-03-27 14:07:40','2019-03-27 21:26:42',1,1,NULL),(166710,'We won\'t participate if Adamawa State supplementary election holds on Thursday - APC','we-wont-participate-if-adamawa-state-supplementary-election-holds-on-thursday-apc','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"We won\'t participate if Adamawa State supplementary election holds on Thursday - APC\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b76d61fb16.JPG\" style=\"height:324px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Roughly 24-hours to the supplementary elections in Adamawa State, the All Progressives Congress (APC) has threatened to ditch the exercise if the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) insists on conducting it on Thursday. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The statement is coming after vacation of an interim injunction that stopped the conduct of the supplementary election on March 23, 2019. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Alhaji Ahmed Lawan, Organising Secretary of APC in the state, made the party&#39;s position known on Wednesday in Yola, the Adamawa State capital.&nbsp;According to Lawan, <em>&quot;the party has rejected the Thursday date and communicated its position to the electoral body. We are not going to participate in the election if INEC is going to conduct it on Thursday. I don&rsquo;t know why INEC is rushing, as conducting this election on Thursday will disenfranchise many voters, particularly workers and students who need to go to work and schools&quot;.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>However, the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) through its chairman, Tahir Shebi, said it is ready for the polls. Kassim Gaidam, the Resident Electoral Commissioner (REC) of INEC in Adamawa, said the commission would hold the election as scheduled on Thursday.&nbsp;Gaidam urged all the parties involved to work towards a hitch-free poll.</p>\r\n',12,1,1145,12,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 14:36:56','2019','3','Adamawa State,supplementary election,apc',NULL,'2019-03-27 14:14:09','2019-03-27 21:26:11',1,1,NULL),(166711,'Video: Man apprehended while attempting to rape 15-year-old girl in Lagos','video-man-apprehended-while-attempting-to-rape-15-year-old-girl-in-lagos','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b78d1b6412.PNG\" style=\"height:312px; width:333px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Residents of Egbeda, Lagos state, today apprehended a man who tried to sexually assault a lady in a hotel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Facebook user, Kathlyn Eyitemi, who shared the video online, said according to the report she got, the victim was running from abuse at her sister&#39;s&nbsp;and she met the suspect who offered to assist her. He took her to a hotel and tried having sex with her. It was when she was struggling with him that the guests in the hotel came out and rescued her.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read what she wrote and watch the video of the man confessing below</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>Barnabas mclinton called me this morning and sent me this video.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Here&#39;s what he wrote------</p>\r\n\r\n<p>-------------</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I slept at this hotel last night at Egbeda. Early this morning sometime around 7am I heard shouting from the room next door. Came out and saw the manager already by the door knock. I heard a female voice shouting from inside so I rushed out forgetting I was on briefs.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>I joined to bang the door till the male occupant opened the door when I threatened I was a police officer.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This idiot tried to rape a 15 year old teenager who was running away from abuse at her sister&#39;s and wanted to go to her mother&#39;s. The fool offered to help the girl, told her to join him to an hotel where she&#39;ll bathe and have something to eat before going to her mother&#39;s.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But as usual such predators have something else in mind....</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9b7937910bf.PNG\" style=\"height:366px; width:489px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned=\"\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Bvg0_Reg08u/?utm_source=i