normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\">Please disregard this malicious propaganda, Dunamis is not responsible.&nbsp;</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"-webkit-text-stroke-width:0px; margin-bottom:0.0001pt; margin-left:0in; margin-right:0in; margin-top:0in; text-align:start\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"color:#222222\"><span style=\"font-style:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures:normal\"><span style=\"font-variant-caps:normal\"><span style=\"font-weight:400\"><span style=\"letter-spacing:normal\"><span style=\"orphans:2\"><span style=\"text-transform:none\"><span style=\"white-space:normal\"><span style=\"widows:2\"><span style=\"word-spacing:0px\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff\"><span style=\"text-decoration-style:initial\"><span style=\"text-decoration-color:initial\"><span new=\"\" roman=\"\" times=\"\">Thank you and God bless you.</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n',12,1,2839,22,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 18:13:41','2019','3','paul eneche,dunamis church.,propaganda',NULL,'2019-03-27 17:24:23','2019-03-27 21:27:28',1,1,NULL),(166729,'Court jails seven yahoo boys, school principal and convicts company for fraud','court-jails-seven-yahoo-boys-school-principal-and-convicts-company-for-fraud','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Court jails seven yahoo boys, school principal and convicts company for fraud\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9ba5c8589ef.JPG\" style=\"height:326px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Uyo Zonal Office of EFCC on Tuesday March 26, 2019, secured the conviction of seven internet fraudsters, popularly called &#39;Yahoo yahoo boys&#39; before Justice S. A. Amobeda of the Federal High Court, Calabar, the Cross River State capital.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The convicts namely: Unamba Maxmillian Chukwubueze; Kingsley Isaacs, Ikenna Madagascar, Obioha Ikenna, David Okpere, Kanu Uchechukwu and Clement Okeke, all indigenes of Imo state with the exception of Okeke who hails from Enugu state were arrested on Friday, February 8, 2019, following intelligence reports, which led to a raid on their apartment on N15a Old Ring Road, off Atiku Abubakar Road, Uyo Akwa Ibom State, which also doubles as their office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justice Amobeda convicted the internet fraudsters after they pleaded guilty to the one count charge preferred against them by the EFCC and subsequently sentenced them to six months imprisonment each with an option of N100,000 (One Hundred Thousand Naira) fine each.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The judge also ordered the forfeiture of the computers, laptops and all other instruments they used in committing fraud to the Federal Government of Nigeria. The convicts had earlier entered into a plea bargain agreement with the Commission in its Uyo Zonal Office.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a related development, Justice Okon A. Okon of the State High Court 7, Uyo, the Akwa Ibom State capital on Monday, March 25, 2019, convicted and sentenced a company, CMD Remediation Nigeria Limited, owned by one Mr. Chikelue Ezechukwu for issuance of dud cheque to the tune of N16, 000,000 (Sixteen Million Naira). A two count-count charge was preferred against the company.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The conviction was also based on a plea bargain agreement. The sentence against the company was a fine of N30, 000 (Thirty Thousand Naira only) on count one, and N20, 000 (Twenty Thousand Naira only) on count two, and a full restitution of the said sum to the complainant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;In line with the plea agreement, the accused has been convicted having restituted the nominal complainant the entire sum being N16, 000,000&quot; Justice Okon stated. Also, Justice Joy I. Uwana of Akwa-Ibom State High Court One, sitting in Ikot Ekpene has convicted the principal of Federal Government College, Ikot Ekpene, Mr. Festus Enyima Dappa on a two-count charge levelled against him by the EFCC.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Commission had dragged Dappa to court on March 7, 2019 for illegally diverting into his personal account, funds meant for construction work in the school and for production of students&#39; year book, amounting to N4. 460million and N2.619million respectively into his personal account. Dappa was sentenced to one year imprisonment each on the two-count charge without an option of fine.</p>\r\n',12,1,1146,3,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 18:12:27','2019','3','yahoo boys, school principal,fraud,seven',NULL,'2019-03-27 17:33:46','2019-03-27 21:27:28',1,1,NULL),(166730,'President Buhari celebrates Asiwaju Bola Tinubu on his 67th birthday','president-buhari-celebrates-asiwaju-bola-tinubu-on-his-67th-birthday','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><br />\r\n<img alt=\"President Buhari celebrates Asiwaju Bola Tinubu on his 67th birthday\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9ba7081f3bf.JPG\" style=\"height:325px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>President Buhari</strong> has sent&nbsp;warm felicitations to the National Leader of All Progressives Congress (APC) <strong>Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu</strong> on his 67th birthday that comes up on March 29th, 2019, describing him as one of the strong pillars of Nigeria&rsquo;s democracy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Buhari joins the APC family in celebrating the Asiwaju of Lagos, who is also the <strong>Jagaban </strong>of <strong>Borgu Kingdom</strong> in Niger State, for his selflessness in serving his country, and making life better for many.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The President recalls some of the sacrifices of the party chieftain to include standing up against injustice in 1993 when the June 12 elections were annulled, which led to his going on political exile for many years, and a protracted legal battle with the Federal Government when funds for Lagos were withheld.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Buhari affirms that Asiwaju&rsquo;s uncompromising posture in the face of injustice and refusal to follow the path of least resistance for personal gains stand him out today as a rare breed and one of the cornerstones of Nigeria&rsquo;s democracy, especially with his track record of persistence, consistency and effective leadership.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As the father of modern Lagos State, the President commends the visionary and inclusive leadership style that the Asiwaju provided for the commercial nerve centre of Nigeria for eight years, laying the foundation for a modern and technologically driven city, and ensuring that every successive leader in the state sticks with the masterplan of a greater Lagos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>President Buhari rejoices with family members, friends, political and business associates of the Jagaban on this auspicious milestone, which is further brightened with the many successes recorded at the recently concluded polls by his strong leadership.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The President believes the best years of the APC National Leader are still ahead, praying that the almighty God will grant him longer life, good health and more wisdom to keep serving the country he loves so much.</p>\r\n',12,1,752,13,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 18:07:51','2019','3','President Buhari,Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu,Jagaban ,Borgu Kingdom',NULL,'2019-03-27 17:38:46','2019-03-27 21:27:09',1,1,NULL),(166732,'Check out this beautiful moment between Aisha Buhari and Dolapo Osinbajo','check-out-this-beautiful-moment-between-aisha-buhari-and-dolapo-osinbajo','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Check out this beautiful moment between Aisha Buhari and Dolapo Osinbajo\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bab9426863.JPG\" style=\"height:335px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Drop your best caption below....</p>\r\n',12,1,2291,21,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 18:07:28','2019','3',' Dolapo Osinbajo, Aisha Buhari,beautiful moment',NULL,'2019-03-27 17:58:45','2019-03-27 21:27:15',1,1,NULL),(166733,'Photo: EFCC docks man for love scam','photo-efcc-docks-man-for-love-scam','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9baa820b246.jpg\" style=\"height:332px; width:333px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission,EFCC, Lagos Zonal office, today arraigned one Omotayo Tapere before Justice Mojisola Dada of the Special Offences Court sitting in Ikeja, Lagos State on a two-count charge bordering on possession of document containing false pretence and forgery.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the counts reads:<em><strong> &quot;That you, Omotayo Tapere (aka Robert Fine), sometime in 2018 at Lagos, within the jurisdiction of this Honourable Court, had in your possession fraudulent email sent from Robert.fine231101@gmail.com, your email account to Fredrica Fox through her email,Frederica2014@hotmail.com titled &quot;I am in love&quot;, professing love to her, a representation you knew to be false.&quot;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The defendant pleaded not guilty to the charge when it was read to him.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In view of his plea, prosecution counsel, M.A. Bashir, asked for a trial date and prayed the court to remand the defendant in prison custody pending the determination of the case.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Counsel to the defendant, Oye Akanni, however, told the court that a bail application had been served on the prosecution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>He, therefore, urged the court to admit his client to bail in liberal terms.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In his response, the prosecution counsel, Bashir, urged the court to allow him to respond to the bail application, saying, &ldquo;My Lord, the prosecution is still within the time provided by Law to respond to the bail application filed by the defendant.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Justice Dada adjourned the case to April 17, 2019 for hearing of the bail application and commencement of trial.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The defendant was ordered to be remanded in prison custody.</p>\r\n',9,1,832,2,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 18:07:01','2019','3','EFCC,Love scam,Love',NULL,'2019-03-27 18:05:21','2019-03-27 21:27:14',1,1,NULL),(166734,'Khloe Kardashian breaks down over Tristan-Jordyn cheating scandal in explosive \'KUWTK\' Season 16 Trailer (Video)','khloe-kardashian-breaks-down-over-tristan-jordyn-cheating-scandal-in-explosive-kuwtk-season-16-trailer-video-2','<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Khloe Kardashian breaks down over Tristan-Jordyn cheating scandal in explosive \'KUWTK\' Season 16 Trailer (Video)\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bbb4f8e067.jpg\" style=\"border:0px solid black; height:271px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-top:0px; width:360px\" vspace=\"0\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The trailer for the season 16 of &quot;<strong>Keeping Up With The Kardashians</strong>&quot; has been released.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the trailer shared by <strong>Kim Kardashian</strong> on Wednesday, it started with a tearful <strong>Khloe Kardashian</strong> reacting to her now ex-boyfriend <strong>Tristan Thompson</strong> and <strong>Jordyn Woods</strong>&#39; cheating scandal.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;It just sucks that it has to be so public,&quot; tearful Khloe sobs right at the top. &quot;I&#39;m not just a TV show... like, this is my life.&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While her mom, Kris Jenner can be heard lamenting: &quot;We just can&#39;t seem to catch a break.&quot; Khloe then yells &quot;My family was ruined!&quot; down the phone at one stage, and has to be physically restrained as she screams &quot;LIAR!&quot; in another.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;Tristan might love me &mdash; whatever that means &mdash; he has no respect for me whatsoever,&quot; she accepts in one moment of reflection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Watch the video below.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-lang=\"en\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\">SEASON 16 <a href=\"https://twitter.com/hashtag/KUWTK?src=hash&amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">#KUWTK</a> MARCH 31 <a href=\"https://t.co/9BJafPbK8H\">pic.twitter.com/9BJafPbK8H</a></p>\r\n&mdash; Kim Kardashian West (@KimKardashian) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/KimKardashian/status/1110936247751471104?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">March 27, 2019</a></blockquote>\r\n',13,1,672,3,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 20:34:13','2019','3','Khloe Kardashian ,Kim Kardashian,Khloe Kardashian,Tristan Thompson,Jordyn Woods,Keeping Up With The Kardashians',NULL,'2019-03-27 19:06:02','2019-03-27 21:27:26',1,1,NULL),(166735,'Breaking: UK Prime Minister,Â Theresa May says she will resign onceÂ her Brexit deal gets approved by Parliament ','breaking-uk-prime-minister-theresa-may-says-she-will-resign-once-her-brexit-deal-gets-approved-by-parliament','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Breaking: UK Prime Minister,Â Theresa May says she would resign onceÂ her Brexit deal gets approved by Parliament \" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bbd6ce1952.JPG\" style=\"height:337px; width:400px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>UK Prime Minister, Theresa May told Conservative lawmakers on Wednesday that she would step down if Parliament approved her plan for withdrawal from the European Union. &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>According to James Cartlidge who was present at the meeting, Theresa May told lawmakers during a party meeting that she &ldquo;will not stay for the next round of negotiations,&rdquo; but did not give a date for leaving.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Another lawmaker who attended the meeting, Simon Hart, said, &ldquo;she made clear that providing the withdrawal agreement is passed she would start the process of an orderly handover.&rdquo; &nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The decision to set a time for stepping down had been urged by her advisers as the only way to garner enough votes to get the plan through Parliament. Many Conservatives have been deeply frustrated with her leadership and believe a new leader is needed to lead the next phase of talks with Brussels.</p>\r\n',12,1,799,2,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 20:16:07','2019','3','m',NULL,'2019-03-27 20:04:14','2019-03-27 21:27:02',1,1,NULL),(166736,'Michelle Obama\'s book Becoming set to become the best-selling memoir in history after nearly 10 million copies sold','michelle-obamas-book-becoming-set-to-become-the-best-selling-memoir-in-history-after-nearly-10-million-copies-sold','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"Michelle Obama\'s book is set to become the best-selling memoir in history after nearly 10 million copies sold\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"0\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bc5e97b457.JPG\" style=\"border:0px solid black; height:240px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-top:0px; width:360px\" vspace=\"0\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Former first lady <strong>Michelle Obama</strong>&#39;s best-selling memoir, &quot;<strong>Becoming</strong>,&quot; has sold nearly 10 million copies, and is set to become the best-selling memoir in history.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The parent company of publisher Penguin Random House announced Tuesday.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>&quot;We believe this could be the most successful memoir in history,&quot; said Thomas Rabe, the chief executive of Bertelsmann, a parent company of Penguin Random House, according to the Wall Street Journal.</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>The candid memoir, which was released in November, quickly became a best-seller and one of the most popular books in the World.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In its first week, &quot;Becoming&quot; sold more than 1.4 million copies, Penguin Random House said in November.</p>\r\n',13,1,174,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 21:06:58','2019','3','Michelle Obama,Becoming, Penguin Random House',NULL,'2019-03-27 20:06:33','2019-03-27 21:27:24',1,1,NULL),(166739,'Women narrate some of the horrific things their partners did to them when they were pregnant','women-narrate-some-of-the-horrific-things-their-partners-did-to-them-when-they-were-pregnant','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bca1a20243.PNG\" style=\"height:338px; width:505px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Most pregnant women say the period of pregnancy is the moment when their partners showered them with the most love and care. But for some, it wasn&#39;t so and these women have taken to Twitter to share their stories.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Some of the stories of&nbsp;physical and emotional abuse shared by the women were so horrific that men took to the replies to apologize on behalf of the men who caused them pain.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Read the tweets below.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bca3cc6b06.PNG\" style=\"height:554px; width:510px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bca7951847.PNG\" style=\"height:294px; width:523px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bca8f7915a.PNG\" style=\"height:267px; width:525px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcadaa7f1d.PNG\" style=\"height:168px; width:517px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcaf1934c4.PNG\" style=\"height:139px; width:509px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcb9b04ec7.PNG\" style=\"height:157px; width:510px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcba69c46d.PNG\" style=\"height:237px; width:525px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcbb23050c.PNG\" style=\"height:154px; width:505px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcbbdee5fd.PNG\" style=\"height:164px; width:506px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcbc944b59.PNG\" style=\"height:161px; width:507px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcbd600fa1.PNG\" style=\"height:275px; width:514px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcaba805e9.PNG\" style=\"height:653px; width:529px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bcac6ba1ad.PNG\" style=\"height:584px; width:530px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n',14,1,1364,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2019-03-27 20:56:10','2019','3','physical abuse,emotional abuse,pregnant women,pregnancy',NULL,'2019-03-27 20:16:48','2019-03-27 21:27:29',1,1,NULL),(166740,'\'Some Nigerians order pizza from London to Nigeria via British Airways\'- Minister of Agriculture, Audu Ogbeh says (video)','some-nigerians-order-pizza-from-london-to-nigeria-via-british-airways-minister-of-agriculture-audu-ogbeh-says-video','<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://alexis.lindaikejisblog.com/photos/shares/5c9bccd26e31e.jpg\" style=\"height:212px; width:333px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Minister of Agriculture, Audu Ogbeh, made a startling revelation when he appeared before the Senate committee on Agriculture today Wednesday March 27th.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The minister while making his presentation to the lawmakers, said&nbsp;some Nigerians import everything including pizza from London.&nbsp;According to the minister, those who order for Pizza from London, make the orders in the morning, through British Airways airlines.</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Do you know, sir, that there are Nigerians who use their cellphones to import pizza from London; they buy in London and bring it on British Airways in the morning to pick up at the airport. It is a very annoying situation and we have to move a lot faster in cutting down some of these things.&rdquo; he told the lawmakers</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14.4px\">Speaking further, the Minister said </span></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14.4px\">&#39;&#39;Nigeria is a</span><span style=\"font-size:0.9em\">&nbsp;nation of importers&rdquo;, adding: &ldquo;Toothpick every year costs us 18 million dollars; tomato paste costs us 400 million dollars. Meanwhile, a basket of tomatoes is less than N2,000.&nbsp;</span>The farmers are losing money because the processors do not have enough funds to set up factories. Two factories have started off. I am sure by the end of next year we can comfortably tell the importers of tomato paste to stop.&rdquo;</p>\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\n<p>Watch a video from his presentation below</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captioned=\"\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BvhWj7lA_pR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_medium=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"12\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\">\r\n<div style=\"padding:16px\">\r\n<div style=\"align-items:center; display:flex; flex-direction:row\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color:#f4f4f4; border-radius:50%; flex-grow:0; height:40px; margin-right:14px; width:40px\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display:flex; flex-direction:column; flex-grow:1; justify-content:center\">\r\n<div style=\"background-color:#f4f4f4; border-radius:4px; flex-grow:0; height:14px; margin-bottom:6px; width:100px\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color:#f4f4f4; border-radius:4px; flex-grow:0; height:14px; width:60px\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding:19% 0\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"display:block; height:50px; width:50px\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding-top:8px\">\r\n<div style=\"color:#3897f0; font-family:Arial,sans-serif; font-size:14px; font-style:normal; font-weight:550; line-height:18px\"><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/BvhWj7lA_pR/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_medium=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; line-height:0; padding:0 0; text-align:center; text-decoration:none; width:100%;\" target=\"_blank\">View this post on Instagram</a></div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"padding:12.5% 0\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"align-items:center; display:flex; flex-direction:row; margin-bottom:14px\">\r\n<div>\r\n<div style=\"background-color:#f4f4f4; border-radius:50%; height:12.5px; transform:translateX(0px) translateY(7px); width:12.5px\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color:#f4f4f4; flex-grow:0; height:12.5px; 